{"id":"a5743610-fa3f-4edd-826e-ecd2b15b9727","title":"1509/06/06: footnote 1","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"c2bb37d5-6a24-4b7d-be9a-7c13d5314655","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Not only was the single bell taken away from San Marco, as was said on 30th June, 1498, but it was exiled from the city for 50 years, under pain of any one who should bring it back being declared a rebel. The decree has been published by my valued friend Alessandro Gherardi on page 205 of the Nuovi documenti e studi intorno a Girolamo Savonarola (Firenze, 1878), together with a record of the chronicler of the convent, and a letter of Fra Stefano di Castrocaro; from which documents it results that the chief credit for this restitution belongs to the Gonfaloniere Soderini, and that the occasion of it was the joy at the re-acquisition of Pisa.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"403c283c-8ba8-4cfa-bf38-8286a106e8e5","type":"page","start":0,"end":647,"value":"234","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"816a20db-8015-43b5-bf56-907ed9631495","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":24,"end":27,"value":"b1b6c840-869b-4660-b4d9-d0a3d785f67c","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"0e2862c6-4ac0-41c9-a8ab-ff6b3f9feb26","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":40,"end":43,"value":"c5a3888d-d340-448b-982c-315ca6e75b52","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"618f9b8c-f191-4906-aa72-7ba1bdd5449d","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":45,"end":53,"value":"36624084-7614-4020-b1e5-f62478667769","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"139248d3-1b48-42f7-86b1-b3afef466e05","type":"codex/document-reference","start":63,"end":66,"value":"953d1b50-695f-41e9-8f46-50ac4d0f1ace","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7998d9f4-9eb2-443b-a5cd-d5c641f35bb9","type":"codex/time-reference","start":71,"end":85,"value":"e0042363-8b98-43be-8baf-18547c81df8a","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bf3a6a46-16de-4e90-8c26-1bf691861ed4","type":"style/superscript","start":73,"end":74,"value":null,"zeroPoint":f